<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9805> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9805" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/25> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 257-63" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6290> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6290" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Termed by Appian a subordinate commander along with L. Antonius in Spain (BC 5.54). He held command along with a certain Lucius (see above, on Livius; and Promagistrates, on Cornelius Balbus) when Octavian sent Antonius there. He may be either a Sextus Peducaeus or T. Peducaeus, Cos. Suff. 35." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5666> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5666" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Caesarian governor of Sardinia (App. BC 2.48, title not preserved)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5191> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5191" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The authors of the Lex Mamilia Roscia Alliena Peducaea Fabia (Riccobono, Font. Iur. Rom. A nteiustin. 1. 138- 140, quoted from Lachmann, Rdm. Feldmesser 1.263). See Rudolph, Stadt und Staat im römischen Italien 186ff., esp. 196-198; H. S. Jones, JRS 26 (1936) 270f.; L. R. Taylor, Stud. Presented to A. C. Johnson pp. 68-78, and above, 109, Tribunes of the Plebs, and note 2. The law apparently dealt with the extension of municipal organization in connection with Caesar's agrarian law and the activities of the land commissioners." .
